{{Otheruses|Kawarazuka Kofun Group in Utsunomiya, Tochigi Prefecture|Kawarazuka Kofun in Gyōda, Saitama Prefecture|瓦塚古墳}} {{Infobox Japanese Kofun | name = Kawarazuka Kofun | image = [[File:Kawarazuka Kofun, Utsunomiya. view from west.jpg|280px]] | caption = View from the west | alias = | group = {{ill|Kawarazuka Kofun Group|ja|瓦塚古墳群}}{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}} | location = {{ill|Nagaoka, Utsunomiya|ja|宇都宮市長岡町}}, Tochigi Prefecture (1188 Nagaoka Town and other locations){{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|loc=Introduction}} | coordinates = {{coord|36|36|3.7|N|139|52|54.3|E|region:JP-09_type:landmark}} | type = {{ill|Zenpō-kōen-fun|ja|前方後円墳}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=58}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=110}} | size = Total length: 48 m, width: 38 m, height: 3.3 m{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=8}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}} | burial = {{ill|Yokoana-shiki sekishitsu|ja|横穴式石室}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=58}} | artifacts = Weapons, horse gear, ornaments, earthenware{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|pp=58-59}} | associated_tombs = | construction = Late {{ill|6th century|ja|6世紀}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}} | person = | historic_site = Utsunomiya City Designated Historic Site{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}} | tangible_cultural_property = }}
The '''Kawarazuka Kofun Group''' (瓦塚古墳群) is a cluster of {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳}} located in {{ill|Nagaoka, Utsunomiya|ja|宇都宮市長岡町}}, {{ill|Tochigi Prefecture|ja|栃木県}}. The {{ill|Kawarazuka Kofun|ja|瓦塚古墳}}, a {{ill|Zenpō-kōen-fun|ja|前方後円墳}}, is the primary burial mound in this group, which originally consisted of approximately 40 tumuli but now has around 30 due to development and other factors.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=58}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=110}}
== Overview == The Kawarazuka Kofun was first excavated in {{ill|1898|ja|1898年}} (Meiji 31). The findings were summarized and published in a scholarly paper by {{ill|Yagi Sōzaburō|ja|八木奘三郎}} in {{ill|1899|ja|1899年}}.{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=110}} Following surveys in {{ill|1991|ja|1991年}} and {{ill|1992|ja|1992年}} by Sakuin Gakuin High School's social studies research club, the site was designated a city historic site in {{ill|1995|ja|1995年}}, and local residents initiated preservation activities.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}}
== Features == The Kawarazuka Kofun Group is primarily composed of {{ill|empun|ja|円墳}} distributed along the {{ill|Utsunomiya Hills|ja|宇都宮丘陵}} in a layout following the ridgeline. The burial mounds date from the late {{ill|6th century|ja|6世紀}} to the early {{ill|7th century|ja|7世紀}}.{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=59}} The main tomb, Kawarazuka Kofun, measures 48 m in length and is notable for its double-tier construction, stone mound covering (fukiishi), and rich burial artifacts, including decorative haniwa and earthenware.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|pp=8-9}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}}
== Surrounding Environment == The Utsunomiya Hills area is rich in archaeological sites, including other burial mounds like {{ill|Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|戸祭大塚古墳}} and {{ill|Yaguchiyama Kofun|ja|谷口山古墳}}. The site is accessible by bus or car, with walking paths leading visitors to the mounds.
