{{afc comment|1=trimming these off. the parameter works as "burial" so no need to use "burial"[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 03:35, 28 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|1=added parameters Interred_individual and Mausoleum is planned to be added but I messed up in template editing[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 02:40, 28 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|1=now we have a 'burial' and 'burial goods' parameter. So a lot of these pages might not be marked on our wiki as having unknown parameters. But specifically keeping this comment here in case of import, these parameters should be added to [[Template:infobox ancient site]] rather than deleted from this draft or article[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 02:01, 28 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|1=I hope this is not too annoying but this article is gonna be placed under [[:Category:Pages using infobox ancient site with unknown parameters]] and there is a decent chance these unknown parameters are ones[[Category:marked infobox kofun with unknown parameters]] I want added to the main template like burial chamber structure and burial goods. Please do not use any bots that just remove the unknown parameters without looking at them. This was added through [[Special:MassEditRegex]] to all pages with the category so apologies if it was just some kind of an error like the image parameter being in Japanese[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 06:00, 27 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{Otheruses|Kawarazuka Kofun Group in Utsunomiya, Tochigi Prefecture|Kawarazuka Kofun in Gyōda, Saitama Prefecture|瓦塚古墳}} {{Infobox Japanese Kofun | name = Kawarazuka Kofun | image = [[File:Kawarazuka Kofun, Utsunomiya. view from west.jpg|280px]] | caption = View from the west | alternate_name = | part_of = {{ill|Kawarazuka Kofun Group|ja|瓦塚古墳群}}{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}} | location = {{ill|Nagaoka, Utsunomiya|ja|宇都宮市長岡町}}, Tochigi Prefecture (1188 Nagaoka Town and other locations){{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|loc=Introduction}} | coordinates = {{coord|36|36|3.7|N|139|52|54.3|E|region:JP-09_type:landmark}} | type = {{ill|Zenpō-kōen-fun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=58}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=110}} | area = Total length: 48 m, width: 38 m, height: 3.3 m{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=8}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}} | burial = {{ill|Yokoana-shiki sekishitsu|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=58}} | burial goods = Weapons, horse gear, ornaments, earthenware{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|pp=58-59}} | associated_tombs = | construction = Late {{ill|6th century|ja|6世紀}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}} | person = | historic_site = Utsunomiya City Designated other_designation{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}} | tangible_notes = }}
The '''Kawarazuka Kofun Group''' (瓦塚古墳群) is a cluster of {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun}} located in {{ill|Nagaoka, Utsunomiya|ja|宇都宮市長岡町}}, {{ill|Tochigi Prefecture|ja|栃木県}}. The {{ill|Kawarazuka Kofun|ja|瓦塚古墳}}, a {{ill|Zenpō-kōen-fun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun}}, is the primary Kofun in this group, which originally consisted of approximately 40 tumuli but now has around 30 due to development and other factors.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=58}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=110}}
== Overview == The Kawarazuka Kofun was first excavated in {{ill|1898|ja|1898th year }} (Meiji 31). The findings were summarized and published in a scholarly paper by {{ill|Yagi Sōzaburō|ja|八木奘三郎}} in {{ill|1899|ja|1899th year }}.{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=110}} Following surveys in {{ill|1991|ja|1991st year }} and {{ill|1992|ja|1992nd year }} by Sakuin Gakuin High School's social studies research club, the site was other_designation1 a city historic site in {{ill|1995|ja|1995th year }}, and local residents initiated preservation activities.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}}
== Features == The Kawarazuka Kofun Group is primarily composed of {{ill|empun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun}} distributed along the {{ill|Utsunomiya Hills|ja|宇都宮丘陵}} in a layout following the ridgeline. The Kofuns date from the late {{ill|6th century|ja|6世紀}} to the early {{ill|7th century|ja|7世紀}}.{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=59}} The main tomb, Kawarazuka Kofun, measures 48 m in length and is notable for its double-tier construction, stone mound covering (fukiishi), and rich burial burial goods, including decorative haniwa and earthenware.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|pp=8-9}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}}
== Surrounding Environment == The Utsunomiya Hills area is rich in archaeological sites, including other Kofuns like {{ill|Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|戸祭大塚古墳}} and {{ill|Yaguchiyama Kofun|ja|谷口山古墳}}. The site is accessible by bus or car, with walking paths leading visitors to the mounds.
