The '''Kawarazuka Kofun Group''' (瓦塚古墳群) is a cluster of {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Nagaoka, Utsunomiya|ja|宇都宮市長岡町|12=draft}}, {{ill|Tochigi Prefecture|ja|栃木県|12=draft}}. The {{ill|Kawarazuka Kofun|ja|瓦塚古墳|12=draft}}, a {{ill|Zenpō-kōen-fun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft}}, is the primary Kofun in this group, which originally consisted of approximately 40 tumuli but now has around 30 due to development and other factors.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=58}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=110}}

