The Kawarazuka Kofun Group is primarily composed of {{ill|empun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|12=draft}} distributed along the {{ill|Utsunomiya Hills|ja|宇都宮丘陵|12=draft}} in a layout following the ridgeline. The Kofuns date from the late {{ill|6th century|ja|6世紀|12=draft}} to the early {{ill|7th century|ja|7世紀|12=draft}}.{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=59}} The main tomb, Kawarazuka Kofun, measures 48 m in length and is notable for its double-tier construction, stone mound covering (fukiishi), and rich burial burial goods, including decorative haniwa and earthenware.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|pp=8-9}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}}

