The '''Kawarazuka Kofun Group''' (瓦塚古墳群) is a cluster of {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Nagaoka, Utsunomiya|ja|宇都宮市長岡町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Tochigi Prefecture|ja|栃木県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The {{ill|Kawarazuka Kofun|ja|瓦塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a {{ill|Zenpō-kōen-fun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, is the primary Kofun in this group, which originally consisted of approximately 40 tumuli but now has around 30 due to development and other factors.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=58}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=110}}

== Overview ==
The Kawarazuka Kofun was first excavated in {{ill|1898|ja|1898th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Meiji 31). The findings were summarized and published in a scholarly paper by {{ill|Yagi Sōzaburō|ja|八木奘三郎|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|1899|ja|1899th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=110}} Following surveys in {{ill|1991|ja|1991st year|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|1992|ja|1992nd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} by Sakuin Gakuin High School's social studies research club, the site was Historic Site1 a city historic site in {{ill|1995|ja|1995th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and local residents initiated preservation activities.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}}

== Features ==
The Kawarazuka Kofun Group is primarily composed of {{ill|empun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} distributed along the {{ill|Utsunomiya Hills|ja|宇都宮丘陵|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in a layout following the ridgeline. The Kofuns date from the late {{ill|6th century|ja|6世紀|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to the early {{ill|7th century|ja|7世紀|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=59}} The main tomb, Kawarazuka Kofun, measures 48 m in length and is notable for its double-tier construction, stone mound covering (fukiishi), and rich burial burial goods, including decorative haniwa and earthenware.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|pp=8-9}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}}

== Surrounding Environment ==
The Utsunomiya Hills area is rich in archaeological sites, including other Kofuns like {{ill|Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|戸祭大塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Yaguchiyama Kofun|ja|谷口山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The site is accessible by bus or car, with walking paths leading visitors to the mounds.

