The '''Kawarazuka Kofun Group''' (瓦塚古墳群) is a cluster of [[:en:Kofun|Kofun]] located in {{ill|Nagaoka, Utsunomiya|ja|宇都宮市長岡町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagaoka, Utsunomiya|qq=}}, [[:en:Tochigi Prefecture|Tochigi Prefecture]]. The [[:en:Kawarazuka Kofun|Kawarazuka Kofun]], a [[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]], is the primary Kofun in this group, which originally consisted of approximately 40 tumuli but now has around 30 due to development and other factors.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=58}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=110}}

== Overview ==
The Kawarazuka Kofun was first excavated in [[:en:1898|1898]] (Meiji 31). The findings were summarized and published in a scholarly paper by {{ill|Yagi Sōzaburō|ja|八木奘三郎|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yagi Sōzaburō|qq=}} in [[:en:1899|1899]].{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=110}} Following surveys in [[:en:1991|1991]] and [[:en:1992|1992]] by Sakuin Gakuin High School's social studies research club, the site was Historic Site1 a city historic site in [[:en:1995|1995]], and local residents initiated preservation activities.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|p=1}}

== Features ==
The Kawarazuka Kofun Group is primarily composed of {{ill|empun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/empun|13=User:Immanuelle/Round Kofun|qq=}} distributed along the {{ill|Utsunomiya Hills|ja|宇都宮丘陵|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Utsunomiya Hills|qq=}} in a layout following the ridgeline. The Kofuns date from the late [[:en:6th century|6th century]] to the early [[:en:7th century|7th century]].{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}}{{sfn|Utsunomiya City|1992|p=59}} The main tomb, Kawarazuka Kofun, measures 48 m in length and is notable for its double-tier construction, stone mound covering (fukiishi), and rich burial burial goods, including decorative haniwa and earthenware.{{sfn|Shibuya, Yanagi & Seichi|2019|pp=8-9}}{{sfn|Hanawa|2008|p=111}}

== Surrounding Environment ==
The Utsunomiya Hills area is rich in archaeological sites, including other Kofuns like {{ill|Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|戸祭大塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|qq=}} and {{ill|Yaguchiyama Kofun|ja|谷口山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yaguchiyama Kofun|qq=}}. The site is accessible by bus or car, with walking paths leading visitors to the mounds.

